Robert D. Silverman <bs@gauss.mitre.org> writes:
 
>No, the rumor is true. There is a way to break RSA. One simply factors
>the public key.
>
>Why is this a mystery?
 
True, you can break RSA by factoring the public key (more precisely, by
factoring the modulus which is *part* of the public key).  This is why RSA
is usually implemented with humongous key sizes--there is no known practical
way to factor a number several hundred bits long.
 
